          <p class="small-text">
            Engineering Physics Robotics competition is an event hosted by Engineering Physics department in UBC every year for second year students. Students go through an intensive 13-week summer course to learn about modern technics for designing and fabricating robots. At the end of the course, each team has a chance to compete with other teams with the robot that they have built.
          </p>
          <p class="small-text">
            The competition in 2010 was to build a tape-following autonomous racing robot that can avoid obstacles as they race others. Our robot "Sherman the Tank" successfully beat other robots in the race and advanced to the final round. We were beaten by other team in the final round and obtained second place (14 teams participated that year). Please take a look at the video of the final round, as it was a very intense race!
          </p>
